Description: Floor sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery open vessel; lustrous black glaze; stamped decoration on the inside: one palmette, ring of tongues, and linking tendrils of outer frieze; two reserved bands on underside; inscription incised on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 528)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2013)
